
Week 1: HTML Core Concepts
Day 1 – HTML Structure & Basics

Must-know topics:

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>, <head>, <body>

Headings, paragraphs, links, images
Key interview questions:

What is DOCTYPE?

Block vs inline elements?

Day 2 – Semantic HTML

Must-know topics:

<header>, <footer>, <section>, <article>

<nav>, <main>
Interview questions:

Why use semantic HTML?

<section> vs <article>?

Day 3 – Forms & Accessibility

Must-know topics:

<form>, <input>, name, id, required

alt, aria-label
Interview questions:

Why is name important?

Explain accessibility attributes (alt, ARIA).

Day 4 – Essential HTML Concepts

Must-know topics:

class vs id

data-* attributes

Meta tags: charset, viewport
Interview questions:

Purpose of meta viewport?

What are custom data attributes?

Day 5 – HTML Review + Interview Practice

Practice questions:

What is the DOM?

What are void elements?

How does browser rendering work?

Week 2: CSS Fundamentals (Interview-Critical Topics)
Day 6 – CSS Selectors & Specificity

Must-know topics:

Element, class, id selectors

Specificity rules
Interview questions:

How does CSS specificity work?

Inline vs internal vs external CSS?

Day 7 – Colors, Typography & Units

Must-know topics:

HEX, RGB, HSL

px, em, rem, %
Interview questions:

px vs em vs rem?

How does inheritance work in typography?

Day 8 – CSS Box Model

Must-know topics:

margin, border, padding

content-box vs border-box
Interview questions:

Explain the box model.

What is margin collapsing?

Day 9 – Display & Positioning

Must-know topics:

block, inline, inline-block

relative, absolute, fixed, sticky
Interview questions:

How does absolute positioning work?

When to use position: sticky?

Day 10 – Flexbox (High-Yield)

Must-know topics:

display: flex

justify-content, align-items
Interview questions:

Flexbox vs Grid?

How to center a div using flexbox?

Day 11 – CSS Grid Basics

Must-know topics:

display: grid

grid-template-columns
Interview questions:

What is explicit vs implicit grid?

When to use Grid over Flexbox?

Day 12 – Pseudo-classes/elements & Transitions

Must-know topics:

:hover, :focus, :nth-child

::before, ::after

transitions & transforms
Interview questions:

Difference between pseudo-class and pseudo-element?

How do CSS transitions work?

Week 3: Advanced CSS & Interview Revision
Day 13 – Responsive Design

Must-know topics:

Media queries

Viewport units (vh, vw)
Interview questions:

Mobile-first vs desktop-first?

How to make text responsive?

Day 14 – Specificity, Inheritance & Best Practices

Must-know topics:

Specificity hierarchy

Cascading & inheritance

BEM naming convention
Interview questions:

Why does CSS conflict happen?

Explain CSS cascade.

Day 15 – Final Interview Revision

Review:

Semantic HTML

Box model

Flexbox/Grid

Responsive design

Accessibility

Mock questions:

Explain flexbox to a beginner.

How does z-index work?

What are common accessibility mistakes?